title: ICE: yield in async block

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code ```Rust #![feature(generators)] #![feature(generic_associated_types)] #![feature(type_alias_impl_trait)] trait Service { type Future<'f>: std::future::Future + 'f where Self: 'f; fn spawn<'f>(&'f mut self) -> Self::Future<'f>; } struct Blah; impl Service for Blah { type Future<'f> = impl std::future::Future + 'f; fn spawn<'f>(&'f mut self) -> Self::Future<'f> { async move { yield &1; } } } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.59.0 (9d1b2106e 2022-02-23) rustc 1.61.0-nightly (8d60bf427 2022-03-19) ``` ### Error output ``` error: internal compiler error: compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/universal_regions.rs:547:26: expected defining type for `DefId(0:16 ~ playground[4992]::{impl#0}::spawn::{closure#0})`: `[type error]` ```
